==Old English==
===Etymology===
From genitive of [[carl]] + [[wægn|wǣn]], literally the ‘peasant’s wagon’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'karlez wæ:n/

===Noun phrase===
'''carles wǣn''' ''m''
# the constellation of the [[Great Bear]], [[Ursa Major]]
#:''Carles wæn ne gæþ næfre adune under ðyssere eorþan, swa swa oðre tunglan doþ'': Carl’s Wain never goes under the earth as other constellations do. (''De Natura Rerum'')

